Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Cut @broccoli florets{8%oz} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Thinly slice @chili pepper{1}.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{5%tsp} in a small #pot{} over medium-high heat. Add half the ginger and cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, ¾ cup water, and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, toss broccoli on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of oil and a big pinch of salt and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pat steelhead trout dry with #paper towels{}; season with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a medium #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add trout and cook until skin is crispy, ~{5-6%minutes}. Flip and cook until opaque and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} more. Turn off heat; remove from pan. Wipe out pan.

In a small #bowl{}, combine @apricot jam{1}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, and ¼ cup water.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for trout over medium heat. Add remaining ginger and cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Pour in jam mixture and simmer until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from heat and stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted. Season with salt and pepper.

-- Use pan used for trout here.

Thinly slice trout crosswise.

> Skip slicing trout.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} and season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice and broccoli between plates. Top rice with trout and drizzle with sauce. Garnish with chili to taste and serve.